
[1]huge

   HUGE, a.

   1. Very large or great; enormous; applied to bulk or size; as a huge
   mountain; a huge ox.

   2. It is improperly applied to space and distance, in the sense of
   great, vast, immense; as a hugh space; a hugh difference. This is
   inelegant, or rather vulgar.

   3. In colloquial language, very great; enormous; as a huge feeder.
